{"name":"Line of Scrimmage","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have the body of an icebox, the arm of a blunderbuss and the head of a boulder. Once you get going, nothing can stop you from running roughshod over everyone.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of these roles: blitzer, blocker, catcher, lineman, runner or thrower. You gain one of the following Traits by role:\nAs a blitzer: whenever you Charge or Run towards a foe, attempt a Stunning Blow or Takedown for 0 AP;\nAs a blocker: whenever a foe Charges or Runs toward you, attempt a Disarm or Chokehold for 0 AP;\nAs a catcher: you can Parry ranged weapons with the Throwing Quality, and throw it back as an Opportunity Attack if successful;\nAs a lineman: when you Assist others with Skill Tests, they may flip the results to succeed at the Test;\nAs a runner: add your [BB] to Movement whenever you Charge or Run;\nAs a thrower: when using ranged weapons, you can ignore the Throwing Quality for purposes of Medium and Long Distances. In addition, ignore the Ineffective Quality and add the Pummeling Quality when using pigskin."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"0fBvRuc9i2ks4Whe"}
{"name":"Call to Arms","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Carrying forward their victories (and defeats) in battle, a Quartermaster brings puissance to any party they serve.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail a Navigation or Warfare Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"1x5nuhDOy9KJWk2g"}
{"_id":"23yolAn8Q2AkbXQi","name":"Arcane Magick","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Combing the Æther into energies through sheer force of will and formula, you can harness Magick with but an utterance of a few words.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are solely a practitioner of Arcane Magick. As a consequence, you may never adopt a Profession which has Divine Magick as a Special Trait. In addition, you immediately learn three Generalist Magick spells whenever you enter this Profession. If you gained Arcane Magick from a previous Profession, you learn an additional Generalist Magick spell instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Second Oldest Profession","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"While prostitution is often heralded as the world’s oldest profession, the work of a Forger is said to come a close second. Your handiwork is nearly unparalleled, both by seekers of art and by Fences who know your craft.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any object you counterfeit is treated and appraised at its full value. Furthermore, you may flip the results to succeed at Skill Tests to identify and create counterfeit items."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"2B3kbufi8JBuso2N"}
{"_id":"2Gg5fHQKwF7hoFfr","name":"Learned Devotee","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Monks have spent many candle-lit hours studying the holy writ and ancient histories, laboriously transcribing many languages into the common tongue.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can read, write and speak the language of any creature that is classified as a Humanoid (including player Ancestries). In addition, whenever you suffer Corruption, decrease the number you gain by 1 (to a minimum of one). This means that if you suffer 3 Corruption, you gain 2 instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"2gNUuILpaTdOAUhC","name":"Blessing of Avalon","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Grail Knights are no mere run-of-the-mill knight; they are so much more – stalwartly compassionate, honorable and chivalrous. They are the embodiment of justice, as holy warriors given jurisprudence by the gods above. As a reward for their virtuous ways, fate has decided that Grail Knights alone have a higher cause to serve. Of course, that ‘quest’ is more dangerous, even life-threatening than their standard duties, but with it comes glory and honor for both themselves and their order.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would gain a Fate Point due to your Order Alignment, you gain two instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"33HwMxq506ZISuBM","name":"Alchemical Thaumaturgy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With alchemical instruments, you have learned to mix Wytchstone into liquid, distilling it into a usable Elixir. However, the risks associated with concocting your Elixirs is severely diminished by your innate know-how.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Immediately after concocting an Elixir, roll D100 three times and pick the one you prefer best. In addition, you never suffer the ill-effects of Critical Failures when preparing Elixirs, instead treating it as a failed Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"33tUktLjveWIgYYc","name":"Bookworm","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Antiquarian has spent many years in the dark, cold recesses of libraries reading histories and treatises of far-flung lands and their inhabitants. Although your skin may be pale as parchment from all those years spent scouring bookshelves, your mental acuity is virtually unparalleled.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Multiply your [IB] by three to determine how many Focuses you may possess."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"34jMaOx1ISp6NhEc","name":"Shield of the Blazing Sun","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Emblazoned upon your shield is the symbol of a golden sun. When this holiest of symbols of the Steward is held aloft it serves as both a signal to those who’d dare trespass against you and a means to gird against incoming missile fire.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you suffer Damage from a ranged weapon, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If it lands on face ‘6’, you ignore the Damage as you automatically Parry the missile for 0 AP. Otherwise, you can attempt to Parry as usual. You must be armed with a shield in order to use this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"3nQJHlDgKCTQf7ts","name":"Rabble-rousing","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Effect: Manipulating crowds with inflammatory words is one of the Anarchist’s primary strengths. You foment rebellion with halftruths, interspersed with little white lies to egg others on. It also turns those so incited to their side, raising pitchfork and torch in their stead... that is, until things go terribly awry.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail a Guile or Leadership Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"49IHcA5UZzBagbG7","name":"Artful Dodger","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Guttersnipes were orphaned on the streets and thieve to eat and survive. Some even take up ‘trades’ – such as a chimneysweep or ragpicker– casing joints underneath the guise of an honestworking citizen.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You automatically gain every Focus in the Stealth Skill when you enter this Profession. This means you may exceed the normal limits for Focuses set by your [IB], but for Stealth only."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4CcdhIe51WnLuOAd","name":"Arcana of Elementalism","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Material Realm is made up of four classical elements. Manipulating ‘Chesed’, the green Ætheric wind, Elementalists are able to use the elements to their advantage. When melded together, they are a force that is both beautiful and destructive.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Elementalism. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Elementalism. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Elementalism until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Elementalism and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4OFngpJFCkyia2Fm","name":"Arcana of Transmutation","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have adopted the thaumaturgic arts, learning to Magickally manipulate metals to bend, shape and twist to your very desire.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Transmutation. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Transmutation. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Transmutation until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Transmutation and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"4easSel4qOJovhsY","name":"Distinguished Speaker","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Demagogue’s authority is widely recognized and they often abuse this privilege. Their voice carries weight, motivating those who’d call them an ally and instigating hatred in those who disagree with their policies.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You influence any number of people who can see and hear you clearly with Fellowship-based Skill Tests. In addition, change your Social Status to an Aristocrat."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"50e9efsnnz7kvvFM","name":"Historical Method","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Scholars use primary sources and other evidence to author accounts of the past and the world around them. Their formative knowledge allows them to understand to a preternatural degree the nature of life and the world at large.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may treat all Intelligence-based Special Skills as Common Skills instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"530yhwh8NuF307vA","name":"Häns Shot First","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Every Smuggler is ruthless at heart, resorting to villainy when the situation necessitates.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When combat begins, you gain 3 APs that must be used immediately at the top of the Initiative Order – even if you were Surprised. Once spent, determine your place in the Initiative Ladder and take your Turns normally. If more than two Smugglers are present, the one with the highest [PB] goes first."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5mxt6r9NuWMh2lu8","name":"Prayers of the Leviathan","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whereas most maritime shanties are sung while passing time aboard a ship, the chanting of the Drowned Ones are haunting invocations. They call forth both below the sea and to the sky, invoking blessings to ensure safe harbor and passage aboard the water.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Leviathan. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Leviathan. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Leviathan until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Leviathan and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"5uWZusrIzzje6KOf","name":"Swagger Wagon","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With a sly smirk, you are not belabored by heavy loads, able to nearly drive a cart or wagon without the aid of an animal. Your friends may even liken you to a donkey or mule, both stubborn to convince, but with a verve and aplomb that others cannot step up to.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Add 3 to your Encumbrance Limit. In addition, you may optionally substitute your Brawn in place of your Willpower when it comes to determining your Peril Threshold."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6PEZjj8jRcPdc18Z","name":"Aimless Drifter","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Consigned to the life of a wanderer, you have seen far-flung places, shook hands with strange people and picked up odd affectations along the road, but as an experienced traveler, you know that road. In that, you’re oftentimes viewed with apprehension or adoration, depending on who you speak with.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Folklore or Navigation Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6j1bdIJHsoss947n","name":"Mettle & Steel","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Squires undergo harsh and rigorous training, lessons which a knight instills into them with vicious beatings at the end of a wooden sword. This regimen teaches them the skills they need both on and off the battlefield through practice, evolving into muscle memory.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At your option, you may substitute the Warfare Skill in place of Resolve. In addition, you may substitute Warfare in place of any Skill required to Resist Perilous Stunts."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"6xMhbzFONySamuDC","name":"Fire and Brimstone","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/burning-eye.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Preacher’s sermons are filled with impassioned words, evoking vivid images of sinners in anguish and torment.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Leadership Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. Furthermore, you always influence a number of people with the Leadership Skill equal to three times your [FB] – this includes use of Inspiring Words during combat. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Blessed Sacrament."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7LC7YsdtI0sZ9hHJ","name":"Call of Duty","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Military Officer is the consummate soldier: they make their beds nightly, they spit-shine their boots with a mirror-like finish, they sharpen their blades razor sharp and they fletch their arrows until the shaft is true. This level of perfection is rarely ever seen among the rank and file, marking Military Officers as more than just a warrior – they are soldiers!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Martial Melee or Martial Ranged Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7bQJjIN29rn4vt98","name":"Arcana of Necromancy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You wield the most unnatural of arts: command over the undead. In your ‘noble’ pursuit to live forever, you have learned to extend life and end it at a whim.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Necromancy. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Necromancy. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Necromancy until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Necromancy and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7hbSL3txePqSbctr","name":"Divine Magick","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/eclipse-flare.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are a proxy to a distant god, calling for divine intervention with the utterance of sacred prayers.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are solely a practitioner of Divine Magick. As a consequence, you may never adopt a Profession which has Arcane Magick as a Special Trait. In addition, you immediately learn three Generalist Magick spells when you enter this Profession. If you gained Divine Magick from a previous Profession, you learn an additional Generalist Magick spell instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"7rwCNLskqeUN4mkM","name":"The Slayer’s Path","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The world is a dark place, filled with loathsome abominations. When these fiends appear, the terrified populace calls upon madmen known as Slayers to kill them. They are foe hammer to such beasts, attacking with relentless furor!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After you have successfully defeated a creature (providing it is not a Humanoid or of a player Ancestry), its kind then becomes your chosen enemy. When attacking your chosen enemy, you always add a 1D6 Fury Die to melee weapon attacks. In addition, you are immune to the Intimidate Skill – along with Stress, Fear and Terror – used by these creatures. Note that there is no upper limit to the number of chosen enemy types a Slayer can have."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Covenant Magick","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have permanently bound your soul to a single Daemon and can harness its forbidden power.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are now a practitioner of Covenant Magick and ignore any Drawbacks your former Arcane or Divine Magick-using Expert Profession required of you (but may continue using your old Magicks). You can now attempt to learn spells from the Covenant linked to this profession, as indicated in the rule book. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from this Covenant. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from this Covenant unless you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can only learn new spells of this Covenant and Generalist Magick from this point forward."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"7xtxO5xA5ouHjMWs"}
{"_id":"82gxzQJjRacdkBWB","name":"What’s Yours is Mine","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Merchant Lords buy what they want, running roughshod over all those who’d stand in their way. For them, there are no critical errors or failure; there is only opportunity.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you Critically Fail any Skill Test, immediately turn it into a Critical Success. However, you suffer 3 Corruption in kind."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Holy Raiment","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Although you may not harness the Magicks granted by a deity, you are no less blessed by your god. Living a hardscrabble life upon the road, the religious habit you wear and symbol you carry are blessed, safeguarding you against wrongdoers.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you wear the robes of your office and bear a holy symbol around your neck, add +1 to both your Damage and Peril Thresholds. Furthermore, you may add the Defensive Quality to any weapon you wield."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"8YUSzoy7SjxI4RHW"}
{"_id":"8yOZkICa1v72voAK","name":"The Fiery Heart","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Winds of the Æthereal Veil burn bright within your heart, invigorating your passion.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You and any non-living possessions carried cannot be harmed by non-Magickal fire."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"97fgTQjkP42j2kPQ","name":"Light the Darkest Hour","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Arcana of Luminescence and thus Hierophants are most potent during the daylight hours, for this is when they absorb the Ætheric power of Luminescence. They can then focus this into immense, often violent, explosions of might and power when they cast Magick.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"During daytime, you may Channel Power without suffering the risk of Chaos Manifestations."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"By Crook Or By Hook","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"There is a willingness to Apostles to spread their faith by all means necessary. Others protest at such unethical approaches, but that’s generally because they’re being berated while suffering the Apostle’s wrath.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you deal Damage with a weapon, you also inflict an equal amount of mental Peril. This only affects creatures that are classified as a Humanoid or Mutant (including player Ancestries)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"AZJ2L1HG1j5WA38m"}
{"_id":"AiviwuMvNMgLfoHP","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Canny, smart and devious, the Footpad can creep along quickly, and catch their victim off guard with a precision strike.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever foes are Surprised or outnumbered 6:1 or more, add an additional 1D6 Fury Die to Damage you do against them. You must use a weapon with the Fast Quality. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of Stealth, you do not have to add the additional 1 AP cost."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Deadly Beauty","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Courtesans are particularly adept at capturing the attention of others, and all eyes turn towards them as they enter a room. You possess an unnaturally radiant countenance, as if you were painted by the finest of Maestros to be the very image of perfection.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"By succeeding a Charm Test, a single person who can see you clearly is Captivated, and will come towards you. Should they enter a dangerous area to approach you, they can attempt a Resolve Test to Resist this effect. Once they are Engaged with you, the effects end. Captivation can only affect Humanoids and Mutants (including player Ancestries). Finally, the same person cannot be made subject to Captivation more than once in any 24 hour period."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"BLRA6sZP5RMEEGLf"}
{"_id":"BsbN7WplylEuAMEI","name":"Prayers of the Winter King","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Magicks of the Winter King require the loudest of exaltations; a combination of howling, stomping of boots and battle cries. There is nothing subtle about the prayers of the White Wolves. Many say that the terrifying priests of the Winter King could call beasts of all sorts forth from the wilds. They may be right.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Winter King. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Winter King. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Winter King until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Winter King and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"C8TQeABeuIDNBrv0","name":"I’ve Seen Worse","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"In tense situations, Veterans are well-equipped to get the job done. When facing all but the direst of straights, a Veteran is stoic and unflappable in the face of danger.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You always succeed at Skill Tests to Resist the effects of Stress and Fear. In addition, you can never be made subject to the effects of the Intimidate Skill."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CJBZoGKpRJjOgQHn","name":"Mortality Work","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With the tools of murder, a Vigilante savors all the ‘little’ emotions of the kill. In their last moments, people show you who they really are, particularly when you have a knife pressed against their throat.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you inflict an Injury with a weapon, your foe also suffers 2D10+your [WB] mental Peril."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CLBKzmLXUtlOdKYL","name":"Here Comes the Cavalry","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether on parade, participating in competitive sports or during times of war, you have mastered the art of equestrianism. This mastery is unparalleled, dwarfed only by your contemporaries whom taught you to ride.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Handle Animal or Ride Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of Ride, you do not have to add the additional 1 AP cost."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Doktor Mind-Bender","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"While hypnotism can lead the insane toward the path of sanity, the power of your voice can also force others to do things more unsavory.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you perform Hypnosis, the patient is also Entranced. While Entranced, the person can be commanded to take any single action you desire over the next week (e.g., quack like a duck, steal a carriage, poison your lord). Should they be commanded to undertake a dangerous task, they can attempt a Resolve Test to Resist this effect prior to taking the action. Once the action has been taken, they are no longer Entranced. Entrancement can only affect Humanoids and Mutants (including player Ancestries). Substitute Heal in place of Incantation when using Perform Hypnosis. Finally, the same person cannot be made subject to Entrancement more than once a week. Performing Hypnosis can be found in Chapter 4: Liber Alchemiae."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"DD20GqCHKDTZxDGv"}
{"name":"Final Benediction","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"In place of the Daemon Prince, you shall have me! Not dark, but bewitching and beauteous as the dawn! All shall adore me, and bask in my light of despair!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you Critically Succeed at casting a Magick spell from your Covenant, you inspire Stress if it is Petty Magick, Fear if it is Lesser Magick and Terror if it is Greater Magick. Foes can attempt to Resist its effect by making a successful Resolve Test. Once a foe has been subjected to Stress, Fear or Terror from the casting of this spell, they cannot be subjected to it again until after 24 hours have passed."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"DWEC9Xm1f06rUPuw"}
{"name":"Religious Fervor","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The power of a Fanatic’s beliefs are so real that they manifest in supernatural ways.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of these three sects: flagellant, heretic or zealot. You gain one of the following Traits by sect:\n   As a flagellant: for every Injury you are suffering from, add a cumulative +1 to Damage Threshold (until reaching +6) – this includes Injuries you inflict upon yourself;\n   As a heretic: you may Counterspell Divine Magick spells, substituting Interrogation in place of Incantation – if you Critically Succeed, the spell instead affects the caster;\n   As a zealot: whenever you or an ally render a foe of an opposing faith Slain! in combat, add a cumulative +1 to Damage (until reaching +6). Only enemies who are classified as Humanoids or Mutants (including player Ancestries) counts toward these cumulative bonuses. Once combat ends, this bonus resets to 0."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"DrWTwPCalp60LK9a"}
{"_id":"DweV62yrsDHZtzsl","name":"Eldritch Signs","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have peered towards the skies in hope of answers, both earthly and sorcerous. In that, the mysteries of the zodiac reveal their terrible truths.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You automatically gain all of the following Focuses in the Incantation Skill whenever you enter this Profession: Astrology, Card Reading, Dream Interpretation, Hypnotize, Palmistry, Scapulimancy and Scrying. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Magick Circle."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"DwmjwLuj76RwMhef","name":"Feast or Famine","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Camp Follower can prepare hearty feasts, re-shoe horses, stitch up torn clothing, empty chamber pots and attend to any number of other mundane activities that lift the morale of those around them. They are a fixture of any successful band of adventurers, well-compensated for their work.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can attempt a Survival or Tradecraft Test to cook for others. If successful, a number of allies equal to your [FB] move one step up the Damage Condition Track positively, and recover their Peril Condition Track to Unhindered, whether they’re resting in a dangerous place or not. If your roll is a Critical Success, you affect a number of allies equal to three times your [FB] instead. A Character may only gain the benefit of this meal once per day, which takes an hour of time to prepare."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"The Black Art","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are a practitioner of the ‘black art’, a simple yet deceptive form of prestidigitation where your hands\n  move lightning-quick.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Skulduggery Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. Furthermore, you may substitute Skulduggery in place of any Skill required to Parry melee\n  weapons."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"E2SOuhLAO1fExrCJ"}
{"_id":"E6Kp9RHRoX0qdPVg","name":"Shield Wall","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Man-At-Arms can form a protective wall of defense, safeguarding their comrades from harm. While armed with a shield and you stand side-by-side with a chosen ally, you can shield them from incoming attacks.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When Engaged with an ally and they fail to Parry or cannot do so, you may immediately Parry in their stead for 1 AP. If successful, they suffer no Damage (and neither do you). You must have a shield in-hand in order to use this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Primal Rage","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Through intense focus, you can channel the might, speed and intelligence of the Primeval your clan has bound themselves to.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of these spirits: attercap spider, barrel- bellied orc, death bat, dire rat, howlbear, silverback warg or water panther. You gain one of the following Traits by spirit:\n   For an attercap spider: you gain the Inescapable Trait from the self-same creature (as found in the Bestiary chapter of ZWEIHÄNDER);\n   For a barrel-bellied orc: you gain the Chomp Trait from the self-same creature (as found in the Bestiary chapter of ZWEIHÄNDER);\n   For a death bat: you gain the Dark Sense Trait from the self-same creature (as found in the Bestiary chapter of ZWEIHÄNDER);\n   For a dire rat: you gain the Disease-Ridden (Bloody Flux) Trait from the self-same creature (as found in the Bestiary chapter of ZWEIHÄNDER);"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"E9RoEUeJx1pejbzc"}
{"_id":"EST4S3D2WCBq66zz","name":"Salty Dog","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether on sea or land, Buccaneers can outmaneuver their foes while throwing themselves into dangerous situations. Whether they be true pirates or even privateers, these salty dogs have learned to take their licks.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"After you make an Attack Action with a melee weapon possessing the Finesse Quality, immediately make an Opportunity Attack with any one-handed ranged weapon on the same Turn. The weapon must already be loaded or in-hand."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"F0MWixUsPbk44nyb","name":"Witch Hunter’s Insight","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"By all that is divine, the Inquisitor metes out justice upon those who offend the gods. You are therefore protected against corruption, in its many forms. You can sniff out all forms of chaos, Ætheric or otherwise.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are always under the effects of the Generalist Magick called Wytchsight. However, you retain your normal vision, able to ‘turn off ’ this sight on command."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FKzXGGzKRO4eILeY","name":"Nimble Fingers","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Burglar’s hands are precious tools and most spend years honing their innate dexterity.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You drastically reduce the time required to use Skulduggery Tests, taking no more than a minute for complex actions (examples include picking locks, pilfering goods, etc.). In addition, you may flip the results to succeed at Skill Tests to steal."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FNGKPP4rskZbDsDL","name":"Grease the Wheels","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Cheapjack knows all the right notes to hit when buying and selling goods. You also know people in the criminal world, and can fence goods fast and cheap.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail a Bargain or Counterfeit Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"G3Wc6d51qB5wFVkJ","name":"Pound of Flesh","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Where desperate attempts to bargain fail, you are there to demand harsh compensation.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Intimidate Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when you successfully Intimidate someone, you inflict 1D10+your [WB] in mental Peril. Finally, you may substitute Fellowship in place of Brawn when determining Base Chance of success with the Intimidate Skill."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"G7T8UiS5zKDBvnXC","name":"Winds of Change","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Æther is a powerful, but fickle force. It exists closer in relation to the powers of corruption than most would care to admit. However, as a Diabolist, you have learned to control the emergent chaos, reshaping it into a controlled, orderly force of power.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you would potentially invoke a Chaos Manifestation, you must roll two or more face ‘6s’ on the Chaos Dice to invoke it. Otherwise, ignore the results. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Magick Circle."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Thiefspawn","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are the go-to when it comes to trafficking ‘hot items’ on the black market.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any object you fence is treated and appraised at its full value. Furthermore, you may flip the results to succeed at Skill Tests to identify and sell stolen goods."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"GEziQFsMYqVi8bgL"}
{"name":"Anointed by Chaos","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Slathering your weapon with sacred oil, you call forth to the Prince of Violence to guide your hand. Hopefully, your invocation is answered... but there are no guarantees when you toy with Corruption.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can Channel Power in order to increase your chances to succeed Combat-based Skill Tests. This follows many of the same rules as Channeling Power to cast Magick, but with these specific requirements: you must have a weapon in-hand, you must be able to see and speak and a phial of sacred oil must be poured onto the weapon. This sacred oil is determined by your GM, based on the weapon you intend to bedevil with chaotic might.\n  You may Channel Power up to three steps. However, if you generate one face ‘6’, you invoke a Petty Manifestation. If you roll two face ‘6s’, you invoke a Lesser Manifestation and if three or more face ‘6s’, you invoke a Greater Manifestation. Furthermore, if a Chaos Manifestation\n  inflicts any sort of negative effects upon you to Cast Magick, apply them instead to your Combat-based Skill Tests. The GM will change the effects of the table to best match\n  the mechanical results."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"Gg91rlrrm4Uww4nT"}
{"_id":"H5PaP5SYmW8aaqfC","name":"Arcana of Animism","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your arcana is of the bestial essence, untouched by the guiding hand of civilization. It flows freely like water, spilling over rock, rupturing the ground and making a way where it can from its source to the sea. Untamed and unchecked, it is neither a force of order or chaos; it is a Wind left free to blow whichever way it wants.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Animism. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Animism. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Animism until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Animism and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"HCFZGUGZ6Bde7cpD","name":"Old Faith’s Chosen","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The’ Old Faith’ is far more ancient than today’s religions; just as it has survived to this day, there are also creatures who have lived these long ages. Such beings recognize your devotion to the old faith and although they will not necessarily regard you as friendly, you are at least harmless, much in the same way that an elephant will regard an ant. In addition, a spirit animal becomes your constant companion, never far from your presence.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Animal creatures classified as Critters will never make you a target of attacks, until you initiate violence towards them or their allies. In addition, you gain the loyal service of a liaison to the Demiurge called a Spirit Animal. This Spirit Animal takes the shape of any small, common creature you can envision. You share an empathic link to the Spirit Animal, up to one mile away. In addition, you can use the Spirit Animal as an Æthereal conduit, using it as an extension of yourself for sight, hearing and touch when it comes to casting Magick (providing it remains within your line of vision). Fortunately, the Spirit Animal can see perfectly in the dark – much to your advantage. The Spirit Animal always miraculously avoids harm by others, turning Æthereal at will. It possesses extremely high intelligence and you can commune with it at any time. Finally, you can project your voice through the Spirit Animal."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Spiritus Sanctus","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Exorcizamus te, omnis immundus spiritus, omnis satanica potestas omnis incursio infernalis adversarii!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When facing a creature that is classified of an Abyssal or Supernatural nature, make an Interrogation Test. If successful, they remain Stunned for a number of Turns equal to your [WB]. However, this only works if the creature can both see and hear you clearly. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Exorcism. Substitute Interrogation in place of Incantation when using the Ritual of Exorcism, but you cannot Channel Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"HSR1fb8Sio3ryPfW"}
{"_id":"Hea13JnmQNvyagtK","name":"Ogham of Truth","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Truthsayers are perfect vessels for order, able to control the Winds of the Æther and become perfectly aligned with divine truth. However, when possessed by the inner turmoil of chaos, Truthsayers begin to waver.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When your Order Ranks are higher than your Chaos Ranks, you never provoke Divine Punishment with Chaos Dice. However, you still gain Corruption by Channeling Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"HrAJnKuFENWjpd1y","name":"True Detective","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Investigator sometimes experiences visions, slivers of petty information which form a loose mosaic in the darkest recess of their mind. They possess the singular ability to disassociate reality and put the pieces of the puzzle back together in a way most don’t even comprehend. Investigators could be geniuses, but they will certainly appear to be lunatics.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When Intoxicated or underneath the effects of Deliriants, make a Scrutinize Test. If successful, you can ask for the GM to give you an important clue from your investigations you may not have already thought of or overlooked. This benefit cannot be gained more than once per day."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"INbi9aCxIOLOZulT","name":"Divine Mastery","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have learned the deepest of secrets in the universe and share an unshakable bond with the gods above. As a result, you have gained (or perhaps earned) the watchful gaze of unsavory deities. Despite this, you are unable to call forth the most earth-shattering of Magicks, invocations unseen by other rank and file priests.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Greater Magick from the list of Prayers your Expert Profession granted you, providing you possess at least three Skill Ranks in Incantation. In addition, you automatically learn one Greater Magick spell from this same list of Prayers."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Younger Futhark","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The secrets of Elder Futhark have been passed down by generations. However, Rune Jarls have mastered a simpler, battle-ready form called Younger Futhark. These runes possess even more power than their forbearers.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You reduce the binding time to one hour for Apprentice Runes, two hours for Journeyman Runes and three hours for Master Runes. Furthermore, the items you inscribe can bear up to 6 Apprentice, 4 Journeyman or 2 Master Runes. Finally, any object you inscribe a Rune upon (including buildings, vehicles or objects larger than a man is tall) takes upon the benefits of the Rune."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"IUWkURAO95yECnyh"}
{"name":"Wyrd Science","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Metal tubes and pots and pans, bits and pieces and magic from the hand, we’re making Wyrd Science!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can use Tradecraft Skill to forge fantastic machines. These machines can take practically any form you can imagine (e.g. horseless carriage called a rumblebutler, flintlock pistol that transforms into a sword, ‘living’ paintings, personal glider, etc.), of which the GM must approve of the design. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Construct Golem. Substitute Tradecraft in place of Incantation when using the Ritual of Construct Golem, but you cannot Channel Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ItkzHMytUGQrRoh2"}
{"_id":"K4qyZGzqXYdPMZmH","name":"Thrice-drowned","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have been blessed by another of your order, forcibly drowned three times. Thrashing as the Leviathan’s salty brine filled your lungs, you saw the truth of the world below the water. Darkness came, and then enlightenment. Each time you were revived by the Kiss of Life, a new mystery was revealed to you. Each dream you had while dead showed you strange, terrible visions of a world that will end in deluge. You must prepare for the end times.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You cannot drown, never suffering from Suffocation when below water. Once you go unconscious, you instead float to the surface. In addition, you may add your [WB] to your [BB] to determine how many minutes you can hold your breath."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Absolve Sin","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Although you do not command divine Magicks, you are charged with a sacred duty: to absolve others of their sinful through penance and acts of contrition.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can spend a Fortune Point to immediately remove a curse or dispel harmful Magickal effects that ail another. In addition, you can spend a Fate Point to immediately reduce another Character’s Chaos Ranks equal to your [WB]. You must be able to touch the person in order for them to be absolved."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"K5swN6oIGe5rj1FI"}
{"_id":"KH6Yc7fRa3LHd9AY","name":"Eureka!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether a crude affair or an extraordinarily complex apparatus, your contrivances are notoriously reliable. As a consequence, you possess an eye for finding the right materials for the job.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Tradecraft Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, you always succeed at Skill Tests to locate resources needed for construction."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"KY1SDD0uGeTKZrqm","name":"Prayers of the Demiurge","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Druids are followers of the Old Faith, a religion that stretches back to the origin of all mankind. You pray at long-forgotten landmarks, such as towering stone monoliths and burial grounds. You now call forth the Demiurge’s grace, bringing forth the primal, elemental fury of the world.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Demiurge. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Demiurge. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Demiurge until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Demiurge and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"KiC8am8KnxhU9VeE","name":"Prayers of the God-Emperor","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You wear the armor of your god and can invoke His prayers. They speak of judgement, righteous fury and execution. You are the God-Emperor’s priest elect and forces of chaos best step aside or else suffer from your holy incantations.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the God-Emperor. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the GodEmperor. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the God-Emperor until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the God-Emperor and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"L3El3HgYaf9xXkuW","name":"Beastmaster","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"While the stench of manure and musk cling to their clothes, the Animal Trainer seems to be akin to the creatures they train. They may even emulate some of their more unusual behaviors, but only for the sake of befriending those same creatures.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can use your Handle Animal Skill to not only tame and train creatures which are classified as Animals, but also those which are classified as Beasts. Whenever you attempt to tame and train Animals and Beasts, you may flip the results to succeed at Handle Animal Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"LMd6Gdbxnobw6AEn","name":"The Bard's Tale","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/burning-book.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you succeed at using Inspiring Words, allies increase their Damage and Peril Thresholds by +1, and add +3 to their Initiative."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cw85KJ7nPukNIXd":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rgPsMfjVxNjTIgA7"}}}
{"name":"Lickety-Split","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"As the old saying goes ‘it is not a sprint, it’s a marathon’. Lithe of limb and spry of spirit, the Messenger is ready to show others that it can be both.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Increase your Movement by +3. In addition, reduce all Movement Actions by 1 AP (to a minimum of 1 AP)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"LsGvWMsafJEA10jQ"}
{"_id":"N8IsIgtjxKodYdr7","name":"Holy Roller","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Doomsayers ritually flog themselves, forging their faith in the crucible of suffering and hardship. Their back may bear many scars, but a Doomsayer knows that the pain they’ve endured guarantees them a place in the afterlife at their god’s side.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Adjust your Damage Threshold by +3, but only when you aren’t wearing armor."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"NKEDnIWEq0HmL10w","name":"It’s a Trap!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With an eye for the minutest of details, traps cannot confound you.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You automatically spot hidden traps without having to make a Skill Test. Furthermore, you may flip the results to succeed at Skill Tests to create and disarm traps."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"NZyL9ddlCpk8VzAd","name":"Guild Privilege","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Artisan’s pursuit of perfection is unparalleled. Whenever they pick up a new trade, it comes easier to them than others.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you purchase a Focus in the Tradecraft Skill, you instead gain three Focuses. This means you may exceed the normal limits for Focuses set by your [IB], but for Tradecraft only."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"O4QkTD79DUgcFo3H","name":"Gunslinger","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With quick hands and practice, you have learned to reload practically every gun with blinding speed. No one can match your skill with gunpowder weapons – save for other Pistoliers. And when Pistoliers test their skills against each other, it all boils down to the draw.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can Load any weapon possessing the Gunpowder Quality as an action for 0 APs. In addition, you ignore the Volatile Quality of weapons that also possess the Gunpowder Quality."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Weather-Worn","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Every Nomad hails from one of three regions. Each region has ‘borne in’ a natural resistance and hardiness into those who grew up in it.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of these regions: northerner, midlander or southerner. You gain one of the following Traits by region:\n- As a northerner: you always succeed at Skill Tests to Resist the effects of physical Peril. In addition, you never suffer from Frostbite;\n- As a midlander: you always succeed at Skill Tests to Resist the effects of physical Peril. In addition, you never suffer from Starvation;\n- As a southerner: you always succeed at Skill Tests to Resist the effects of physical Peril. In addition, you never suffer from Heatstroke.\n  "}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"OUHSVKMiTv5rVBlc"}
{"name":"Insidious Whisper","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whispering but a few words, you compel another to experience feelings unbecoming of their situation or nature.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you are standing next to or Engaged with a person (who can also hear you), you can use your voice to compel another. By succeeding a Guile Test, you force a person to experience an emotion of your choice for a number of minutes equal to your [WB].Suggestions include anger, anticipation, disgust, fear, joy, sadness, surprise or trust. As the emotion is felt, choose whether they move one step up or one step down the Peril Condition Track. Once the experience of the instilled emotion has passed, the person has no memory of who compelled them to do so. Insidious Whisper can only affect Humanoids and Mutants (including player Ancestries). Finally, the same person cannot be made subject to Insidious Whisper more than once in any 24 hour period."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"OgfiXm9RaLBSJNxd"}
{"_id":"OoINtVCCKhtiQXqV","name":"Dogs of War","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Every scar a Sellsword bears has a story behind it. Every disfigurement speaks to their history of violence. But war... war never changes. And every mercenary must debase themselves for survival, doling out barbarity with reckless abandon.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You never suffer Serious Injuries."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"P9TuynBi5GU5UNNP","name":"Faustian Bargain","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your prayers are no longer answered by the god you once knew, but instead one of the vile Abyssal Princes. These personalities whisper dark secrets in your ear, telling of terrifying things to come. To see these ends come to fruition, they have given you a gift of their favor… you just dare not comprehend what they will require of you in return.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you Critically Succeed at an Incantation Test, a single, hand-sized shard of Wytchstone appears in your palm. In addition, you may ignore the divine commandments your previous Expert Profession required of you through its Drawbacks."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"PlnHMTn6xD7OvDIe","name":"Blood & Sand","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The roar of the crowd inspires the Pit Fighter to greatness. Let the lavish spectacle of the sport begin and rally the people to your favor!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you spend a Fortune Point, you move one step up the Damage & Peril Condition Tracks positively."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"QYJYnUWd31tOv7lj","name":"Shades of the Past","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"When you brush your hand over the dead, your head fills with visions from their life. From both joyous and traumatic events of their personal history, your mind reels with memories of the life once lived by the corpse you touched.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you touch a corpse, make a successful Incantation Test to learn three important facts about their past. However, you may only ever exert this power over an individual corpse once."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"R6vRA78FahdbkZHQ","name":"Ulv-skinn","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"To priests of this cult, no other animal is more sacred than the wolf. They represent the primal beginnings of all mankind; intelligent, pack-like huntsmen. By skinning these lupine predators, they can literally ‘wear’ the powers of the wolf, able to speak the tongue of canines and resist the bitter cold.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"While wearing the skin of a wolf, you may use any Fellowship-based Skill to directly communicate with creatures that are wolves, dogs or other beasts of similar nature. This interaction is not always beneficial: many such creatures are skittish, ignorant, confused, cunningly deceptive or even openly aggressive. This empathy acts as a supernatural type of communication; the exact nature and complexity of which is determined by the GM. In addition, while wearing the wolf skin, you never suffer the ill-effects of cold weather or Frostbite."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"RbGV7B07mcMeVG5u","name":"Shadow Broker","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Legal informants and other underworld associates share random information with you freely for the benefits they may yield at a later time. Assembling these dissonant parts, your mind can weave them together to provide significant leverage when the time is right.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At any time, you may spend 1 Fortune Point (or 1 Reputation Point if your GM is using these alternative rules) to gain a critical piece of information from underworld contacts, rumormongers or other sources. Reputation Points and their use can be found in Chapter 11: Game Mastery."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Rs48VtD50n9mZu3r","name":"Situational Awareness","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your road-weariness has turned into a wariness unseen amongst others. You have attuned yourself to the smallest of sounds in the wilds, and can react quickly and efficiently.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail an Awareness or Stealth Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"S2OLCaNFx0zHJRaI","name":"Hue & Cry","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Watchman relies on preternatural instincts to sniff out danger. They are quick to rally in the face of lawlessness, vigilant and alert.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When combat begins, roll 2D10, instead of 1D10, to determine your place in the Initiative Order."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"SJ717bbpKOCR2sru","name":"Nostrum Remedium","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Sometimes, the old ways are best. The Apothecary’s understanding of natural medicines and country remedies produces pure, undiluted concoctions that yield impressive results. You are trusted by wives and husbands as being a medical Doktor in your own right. But a canny chirurgeon may see through any deceptions should you try to ply quackery or fraudulent medicinal potions.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Alchemy Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, you never suffer Peril as a result of failed or Critically Failed Alchemy Tests."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"SMW7egig7QDi05S8","name":"Dauntless","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/sword-brandish.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are immune to the effects of the Intimidate Skill and cannot be Stunned or Knocked Out!"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cw85KJ7nPukNIXd":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JlQlIHZZsQhJJAX8"}}}
{"_id":"SVF4DsF4pHKudLqf","name":"Scrivener’s Speed","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are trained to both to read and write at an alarmingly fast rate, which when combined with your lightning quick intellect, means you understand the written word quickly and easily and are able to replicate just as quickly and accurately.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You reduce the time required to use Education Tests by half (examples include research, speed-reading, writing, etc.). In addition, you automatically succeed at all Skill Tests to decipher cryptographs in languages they understand."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Extra! Extra!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Pamphleteer has their ear to the proverbial ground and when it comes to rumor or gossip, local or from further away, there is no one better to chew the fat with.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Folklore or Rumor Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"SYbHaVzutFjWGKiu"}
{"_id":"T2KTTC93YNYzM8OS","name":"Beggars Bowl","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Hand outstretched, arm in a sling or leg strapped up to show only a stump. Your words and injuries might be honest or conniving and deceitful. Both will be supported by a long, sordid tale of the woes that befell you. Or you’ll harry your mark down the street, demanding compensation for their good fortunes while belaboring how the world is against you. Either way, they’ll drop a pfennig or two into your bowl – if only to shut you up.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail a Guile or Intimidate Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Hellfurnance's Gift","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Once they profess their might, a Sirocco Prophet’s body grows gravid with black, stone-like growths and their voice becomes but a harsh whisper – the sound of tectonic plates slowly moving beneath the earth.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You do not need to be able to speak to cast Magick, use Rituals or Counterspell. In addition, you automatically Resist touch-based spells."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"T8qXC5eGZybZC1tJ"}
{"_id":"Tfg4QZOOzC63UHVl","name":"Arcana of Morticism","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The practitioners of Morticism have a reverence for life and a deep understanding of death. It is the cessation of unnatural endings – such as with Necromancy – an understanding of how time flows, and how destiny affects mortal kind. Morticism is the dusty murk between both that which is living and that which is not; a veil between both the Well of Souls and the Material Realm. If life were summer and death is winter, then Morticism is the fall – a path between where both twains shall pass.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Morticism. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Morticism. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Morticism until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Morticism and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ToRivrdjmrE0V3gt","name":"Face In the Crowd","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"An Illusionist knows how to pass themselves off as another. You can go unnoticed, and possess an uncanny aptitude to make others forget who you are. It is rare that any take heed by your passing and even if they do manage to remember you, what they remember is vague and inconsistent. Thus they chalk up their lack of recall to indifference, faulty memory or both.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Strangers and acquaintances alike must Critically Succeed at a Scrutinize Test in order to recognize you, even if they have met you before. You otherwise always succeed Disguise Tests to pretend to not be who you really are."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"Txv97IoX5ZcKXFQR","name":"Prayers of the Martyr","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Although the Martyr is a very popular goddess, her followers do not preach actively. They merely serve as compassionate volunteers to those truly in need. Water is sacred to every Revered Mother, and is often used to consecrate the thresholds of doors that have been transgressed against by violent people, or used to bless the wounded. Her prayers are of healing and mercy.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Martyr. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Martyr. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Martyr until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Martyr and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Snake Oil","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With a few drops of mineral oil, turpentine and a bit of that “ol’ black magic”, you turn any normal ointment into a miracle liniment.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You treat the Alchemy Skill as a Common Skill. In addition, you may substitute Snake Venom in place of any needed reagent to alchemize consumables (as outlined under Materia Medica from the Hazards & Healing chapter in ZWEIHÄNDER and in Chapter 4: Liber Alchemiae). The only exception to this is when Wytchstone or its byproducts are required as regents."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"UEnfP0hI4hGfWcRV"}
{"_id":"UFWiyvJpg38yXGwL","name":"Prayers of the Nightfather","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Those who worship the Nightfather have no prescribed document of faith nor do they adhere to a religious body. They operate semi-independently of any formal church, although they do maintain a number of ‘shrine clubs’ dedicated to the god of luck. Those lucky enough to be blessed by him can call upon His powers to change the outcome of events in both minor and life-altering ways.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Nightfather. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Nightfather. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Nightfather until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Nightfather and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Aye Aye Skipper","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Both on the sea and by land, you attract both admiration and respect for your position as a captain of the sea.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Navigate Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of swim, add your Initiative value to the Distance you swim."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"UN2ul8jvZLtZu2Al"}
{"_id":"UjCC8vVSSvtqMwyD","name":"Banter & Jibe","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Royal court jester, a slave to humor. Monarch’s entertainer, I’m his consumer. I can only entertain, where my voice can’t be heard. A clown, a joke, a fool – as I am often referred!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Coordination Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, you always succeed at Coordination Tests to perform acrobatics."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Seize The Opportunity","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Spouting a litany of orders, others quickly fall in line under your order. And when words fail, you take it upon yourself to fight.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When Engaged with an ally and they fail to strike, you may immediately use an Opportunity Attack in their stead for 1 AP. You must be armed with a melee weapon in order to use this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"UzAqU5WDKoBbhfKX"}
{"_id":"VOdFxkrNvN5BNbzh","name":"Exsanguinator","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"To spill blood is to please the Crouching One. It invigorates His power from beyond and brings great stillness to the universe. Although a purely chaotic act, it can fill the Bloodmonger with divine jubilance and heal them from their ailments.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you render the killing blow to any creature that is classified as a Humanoid (including player Ancestries), you move one step up the Damage Condition Track positively, but in exchange must suffer 3 Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Precision Shots","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whenever your shots find purchase, you whittle away at your opponent’s ability to react accordingly.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Every time you inflict Damage using a ranged weapon, temporarily increase your Damage by +1 cumulatively, lasting until you are Slain! or combat ends. You cannot wear armor with the Heavy Quality to take advantage of this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"VWwMoT1IKL1ONoD2"}
{"_id":"WFN9ZrRKI5lkCgl3","name":"Four-in-hand","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Coachmen establish a trusted bond with animals and beasts, pressing them onwards when the time is needed. For all they know, you may very well have been a champion cart racer in the past, exhibiting tight skills when in the driver’s seat.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Drive Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of Drive, you do not have to add the additional 1 AP cost."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Bedside Manner","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You’ve given up the spiritual approach of humorism to embrace a more modern (but still questionable) approach to medicinal practice.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you successfully bind wounds, you also move the patient an equal a number of steps up the Peril Condition Track positively. In addition, you always Critically Succeed at Heal Tests to treat injuries (as outlined under Bind Wounds and Treat Injuries from the Hazards & Healing chapter in ZWEIHÄNDER)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"WZPCKhvxAZwisi2A"}
{"_id":"Wx0TZHB8ghGoBzwV","name":"Elder Futhark","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Rune Thanes attest that all language comes from the Elder Futhark, an ancient script found amongst the deepest ruins known. They make it their business to memorize these runes, in hopes of unlocking the secret to ultimate knowledge.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Anytime you use the Ritual of Inscribe Magick Rune, you may flip the results to succeed Incantation Tests during the empowerment cycle. In addition, you automatically understand how to use the Ritual of Inscribe Magick Rune. Finally, you may treat the Incantation Skill as a Common Skill for purposes of Rituals associated with the Skill Focus (Runesmith)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"X5vZmKqBBbv3TT3T","name":"Living Avatar","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"To the laity, the most obvious signs of a god’s divine grace is the Magickal power, or prayers, they grant. Unlike the laity, however, you have attained the succor of your god and a benediction of the favor. Etched deeply within your soul and physically upon your body, a series of stigmata illustrate that you are truly favored above all others.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you sacrifice a Fate Point, permanently add 6% to any one Primary Attribute of your choice."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XGS6f7jTsiYjf7SQ","name":"Arcane Mastery","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Having reached the ultimate stratum of Magickal practice, you now understand the deeper secrets of the Æthereal Veil. Unraveling these arcane mysteries, you call forth powerful, world-altering Magicks, but at the risk of corrupting yourself and harming your allies in the process.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Greater Magick from the list of Arcana your Expert Profession granted you, providing you possess at least three Skill Ranks in Incantation. In addition, you automatically learn one Greater Magick spell from this same list of Arcana."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XKKy1w0zadGHNMK4","name":"I Sell the Dead","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Graverobber has heard and seen their share of strange things over the years; the dead rattling in their coffins, corpses reanimating upon their own accord, the wailing of banshees from crypts and the clanking of a revenant’s chains deep below the earth.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When facing Supernatural creatures, you always succeed at Resolve Tests to save yourself from Stress and Fear provoked by them. In addition, you are immune to specific Diseases such as Red Death and Tomb Rot."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XRZqohblgx1Ua2HU","name":"Art of Invisibility","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Using closely-guarded arts of the Assassin, you can disappear before others’ very eyes.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can attempt to use the Stealth Skill to escape from plain sight, providing you have a distraction. In addition, you automatically succeed at all Skill Tests to blend into crowds, unless you give yourself away by running through them or failing to conceal a drawn weapon."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Border Patrol","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"To ensure the safety of the village, Mootwardens employ skirmisher tactics at range. This keeps both themselves\n  and the people they’ve sworn to protect safe from harm.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one foe in combat. That foe is left Defenseless to all Ranged Attacks and Called\n  Shots made with ranged weapons you make against them until they are defeated. You may select another foe once the current one is defeated."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"XhAIo7sfG0oBnGYL"}
{"name":"Renegade Magick","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your mission is unwavering and unquestionable. You shall bring the Abyssal Princes and their vassals to their knees. In Him, you believe. In you, He trusts.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Your Magick can affect Abyssal & Supernatural creatures, despite not knowing their True Name."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"YqxJEaRY2um9JtZI"}
{"name":"Leaf on the Wind","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With inward focus, you can attune yourself to the world as a combative technique. Taking in all the subtle noises, the rhythm of your opponent’s breathing and movement, you swiftly draw your sword – exhaling “kiai!” – to strike true.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you Take Aim for 2 AP with a melee weapon and successfully strike, roll two Fury Dice and select the better of the two to determine weapon Damage. In addition, you can Take Aim as a Reaction before Parrying attacks. You must attack with a Bladed type of weapon to utilize this Trait, and it must be sheathed before striking."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"YsDLZo6bAojr8AOL"}
{"_id":"ZMu37LXmeEYYhCvA","name":"Pulp Hero","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Explorers are women and men of action; if their derring-do lands them in trouble, then it will get them out again – even if only by the skin of their teeth.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail an Awareness or Coordination Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Grog, Guts & Glory","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You satisfy the Endless Gullet’s hunger by savoring every last drop of booze, blood and befouled water.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are Intoxicated, add +3 to all Damage you inflict. Furthermore, you can consume spoilt or uncooked meat and drink filthy water without getting sick or diseased."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ZiZPG1IXKq4HDmA7"}
{"_id":"Zq0jDmu7M0Rg8RRZ","name":"Alfred Pfennigworth","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Valets embody impeccable grace and confidence, attending to their duties with professional charm while galvanizing the presence of those whom they serve. Their presence mollifies reputation, lends credit to business dealings and ensures seamless social maneuvering.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you Assist others with Skill Tests, they gain two Assist Dice instead, choosing the better of the two to use. In addition, when you Assist them, they may ignore any Critical Failures they roll, treating them as regular failures instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ZzxKSjYqVcQh5UsR","name":"Machiavellian Intrigue","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Political jockeying and subtle manipulation within the higher social circles come second nature to the Courtier. Thus, they have learned to pick up on subtle tells and affectations which gives away true intentions.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail an Eavesdrop or Scrutinize Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"aUVtKZsvrRx3tkKl","name":"Tortuous Inquisition","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Jailer knows every trick necessary to pry information from others. Psychological intimidation is their primary tool; acid, scissors, pincers and thumbscrews are reserved only for the most unyielding of prisoners. Between the bleeding and the screams, the Jailer knows when a prisoner is telling the truth, or simply lying to escape further pain.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Interrogation Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when you successfully interrogate someone, you may inflict any Moderate or Serious Injury of your choice or cause them to suffer from Stress or Fear."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ai9thCxWrS0wK1ny","name":"I Am the Law!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Reeve is so cold, they bleed ice – when they speak, they never need to repeat themselves. There are times when patrolling the roads over windswept moor and through dark forest, when a distinct show of force is necessary to cow a brigand or highwaymen, all it takes is a flash of their badge.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Intimidate Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. Furthermore, you always influence a number of people with the Intimidate Skill equal to three times your [BB] – this includes use of Litany of Hatred during combat."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"alxJAEVLTsg4aIEa","name":"Issue Challenge","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/sonic-shout.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Confronting a Hedge Knight is a dangerous prospect and many foes quickly find themselves pinned down by their valorous onslaught.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one foe in combat. That foe is left Defenseless to all Melee Attacks and Called Shots made with melee weapons you make against them until they are defeated. You may select another foe once the current one is defeated."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ao3psE0jvfrHcHoG","name":"The Show Must Go On","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"An Entertainer may be a poet, a comedian, a playwright, a bunko artist or even a burlesque dancer. They are a vaudevillian at heart, praised and paid for their performances. Whether lifting spirits through words or song, the Entertainer’s positive demeanor is infectious, setting the right mood for others.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can attempt a Skill Test, related to your Focus in the arts, to perform for others. If successful, a number of allies equal to your [FB] gain the benefits of Inspiring Words for 24 hours. If you Critically Succeed, you influence a number of allies equal to three times your [FB] instead. A Character may only gain benefit of this performance once per day, which takes at least an hour of time to perform."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Fair Share","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Love it or hate it, you are a professional hireling. This rough- and-tumble life has taught you a few important lessons before you joined an ‘adventuring party’.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Add 3 to your Encumbrance Limit. In addition, whenever you negotiate your rate of pay, add your [FB] in the type of coins you will be paid in. For instance, if you are being paid as a Stevedore (2bp daily) and have a [FB] of 4, you would be paid 6bp a day instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"bYzGYGYwSvkRf28c"}
{"_id":"bjp2sYN4znizWhwp","name":"Confidence Trick","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Charlatan is ever the opportunist, exploiting the naiveté of the foolish and stroking the vanity of the witless for their own benefit.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Guile Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. Furthermore, you can influence a number of people with the Guile Skill equal to your [FB] times three – this includes using Dirty Tricks during combat."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"The Trials","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Before a person is made a Hexer, they must go through three rigorous trials, culminating in the consumption of intense alchemical decoctions to mutate their physiological selves.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you attempt to Resist Disease\n  or Poisons (including Intoxication), you may flip the results to succeed at Toughness Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Trace Sigil. Substitute Folklore in place of Incantation when using the Ritual of Trace Sigil, but you cannot Channel Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"bsH34A1Uq3mfWpSw"}
{"_id":"c4qKvjMXKmWbTh7y","name":"Mastery of the Void","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You ‘crush’ the unstable Winds of the Æther, forcing them to coalesce into chaotic yet powerful combinations with dramatically amplified effects. However, even as you bend these deeply destructive Winds in the shapes you desire, they can have wildly unpredictable side effects that can unravel the thin veil between the Material Realm and the Abyss, creating unstable rifts.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you Channel Power and succeed at your Skill Test, you Critically Succeed instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cEXHgOaC8rHI5IAR","name":"Arcana of Luminescence","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Luminescence is the most difficult of Ætheric Winds to control. It requires a potent mind, with a deep connection to the inner light of consciousness. When harnessed though, it can be bent into immense displays of light, healing and arcane power.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Luminescence. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Luminescence. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Luminescence until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Luminescence and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cMTH0dgcfu78bw9g","name":"Town Gossip","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Servant is an invisible presence, able to blend into the background around their employers and less reputable members of society. This provides them ample opportunity to eavesdrop, covertly observing others while picking up juicy rumors.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail an Eavesdrop or Rumor Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"cOSJge3JURUkSoke","name":"Rise From Your Grave","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your mastery over life has given you limitless power over the dead. Calling them forth from their graves is a natural part of your research. A host of the undead awaits, ready to heed your call to rise forth, for they are legion.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Anytime you attempt to create or control creatures classified as Supernatural, you may flip the results to succeed at Incantation Tests. In addition, you automatically understand how to use the Ritual of Awaken the Dead. Finally, you can use any Ritual which brings Supernatural creatures under your control within one minute, instead of the normal casting time required."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Wyrding Way","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Grey Vivimancers move through the folds of space-time, metabolising Wytchstone at an immeasurably chaotic rate.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are under the effects of Wytchstone Essence, reduce the number of AP to cast Magick spells of your Covenant by 1. In addition, you never suffer from the ill-effects of using multiple ampules of Wytchblight."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"cXnq5rGcsRrxfO1x"}
{"name":"Coldheart","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Within every Rime Maiden’s breast beats a heart of ice and fire, a gift from their Daemonic mistress.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You always succeed at Skill Tests to Resist Damage and Peril from cold weather. In addition, you take no additional penalties to movement in winter from inclement weather or icy surfaces."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"cdHHHRdEbgyMFXgf"}
{"name":"De Facto","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Burgomaster speaks with their master’s or lady’s voice, and has at their command a breadth of knowledge and tools in negotiation.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Bargain or Education Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"dJqC7XvJ8WDKIKew"}
{"name":"Seasons of Change","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Dirgesingers take upon an aspect of the season they are in. Changeable like the leaves of the tree, both their ability and personality evolve as the months pass.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"During each in-game season, you can take advantage of the following appropriate Traits:\n   In spring, anytime you generate a Critical Success after rolling D100, automatically add one Fortune Point to the Fortune Pool;\n   In summer, at your option you may substitute Incantation in place of any Skill required to Resist Magick spells;\n   In autumn, you never suffer mental Peril as a result of failed Resolve Tests nor Corruption due to it.\n   In winter, whenever you succeed at casting Magick, you do not expend reagents. This benefit does not apply to Rituals."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"e1GQK0acAYIZdLzz"}
{"name":"Bonds of Damnation","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Literally fused with a harness of steel, your body absorbs the metal’s strength as it takes upon the tensile nature and flexibility of muscle. It is now a part of you as much as your bones, skin and blood are.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can metaphysically ‘bond’ with a full suit of armor. By bonding with it, you automatically gain 1 permanent Chaos Rank. Once bonded, you ignore its Encumbrance Value and any negative Qualities it confers. Furthermore, it cannot be destroyed or gain the Ruined! Quality. Finally, the bonded armor does not negatively impact any Skill Tests that would normally be affected by the type you wear (e.g. swimming, sprinting, climbing, Dodging, etc.). This bond can be broken, but you must undergo the ceremony again. Your GM will outline the requirements for the ceremony."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"e4rra5GdPFOVWdzh"}
{"_id":"eET0zHC8LXOo2IFw","name":"Jack of All Trades","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Raconteur can apply the fundamentals of most abilities, even without formal training. They are true factotums, dedicating themselves as a jack of all trades but a master of none.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You gain a +5 Base Chance to all Skill Tests you do not possess Skill Ranks in."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"eM7a0NdiNBY6nM8s","name":"More Work?","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The long, arduous days a Peasant faces never seem to end. Rustic in your ways, you’re well-acquainted with the hardships of labor and have developed a specific tolerance towards backbreaking drudgery. And when you rest, you sleep soundly and always awaken refreshed.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Adjust your Peril Threshold by +3. In addition, you always recover your Peril Condition Track to Unhindered after resting."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"eO6MmWqxOntwpMX3","name":"Gutterspeak","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Maintaining congress with mangy dogs, wild rodents and tending to other varmints, Rat Catchers are often seen talking to themselves. However, they are in fact conversing to the animals they catch and hunt alongside with. They often reply to each squeak, chirp or hiss they hear. Having spent years in tunnels and warrens, they interpret them just as if they were talking to any other person.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may use any Fellowship-based Skill to directly communicate with Small Animals (specifically moles, rats, rabbits, rodents, snakes, weasels and dogs). This interaction is not always beneficial: many creatures are skittish, ignorant, confused, cunningly deceptive or even openly aggressive. This empathy acts as an all but supernatural type of communication; the complexity determined by the GM. In addition, you are immune to specific Diseases such as Filth Fever and Grey Plague."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Soldier of Fortune","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your unpredictable fighting style originates from your mercenary attitude and the many victories you’ve gained in lands both native and foreign.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you make an Attack Action or Perilous Stunt using a melee weapon, foes must flip the results to fail to Dodge, Parry or Resist it."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"eOqx0eATUN3HN8Ac"}
{"name":"Knightly Order","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"There is a multitude of knightly orders, but at their very basic, they are divided into three broad orders.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of these orders: noble, secular or templar. You gain one of the following Traits by order:\n   As a noble Chevalier: whenever you fail a Martial Melee or Education Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome;\n   As a secular Chevalier: whenever you fail a Martial Melee or Ride Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome;\n   As a templar Chevalier: whenever you fail a Martial Melee or Resolve Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"eQ0ZZlpitrF8AncS"}
{"name":"Wharf Rat","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Stevedore passes the drudgeries of the day away with bawdy songs and small contests with their brethren. It may be who can tie a knot the tightest or who can lift the most weight at once without wobbling over.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Toughness Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. Furthermore, you never reduce your Movement due to Overage."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"fJHovRLKACiR7JwF"}
{"_id":"fLTBCoqysYOPzslQ","name":"Batten Down the Hatches","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Boatman can steer a ship, boat, or barge safely through almost any passage.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Pilot Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of Swim, you do not have to add the additional 1 Action Point cost."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fMlvBU8lDKFxExKZ","name":"Sisters of Mercy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Blessed are the Revered Mothers, for they radiate an invisible aura of blue-white Æthereal light. This pallor discourages rational-minded folk, even those touched by Corruption, from harming a Revered Mother. Only when the priest makes the choice to embrace violence does this divine aura fade.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any creature that is classified as a Humanoid (including player Ancestries) must reduce the Damage they inflict upon you by your [FB], until you initiate violence towards them or their allies."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Warmonger","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Raise the shield or be cast into death! Take a final look, your final breath! No turning back, in battle there is no law!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Add both the Punishing and Reach Qualities to all one-handed melee weapons you wield."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"fOcQUOQO8oGS1WaH"}
{"_id":"fRJekzx6Bt4G12S5","name":"Hedgewizardry","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Hedgewise can harness the simplest of the ever-changing Winds of Magick far more naturally than their studiously, wizardly counterparts. They exhibit mastery over the smallest of spells, but maintain an ignorance towards others beyond their understanding.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When casting Generalist Magick – at your option – you may automatically succeed at the Incantation Test, but move one step down the Peril Condition Track negatively. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Magick Circle."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"fZVlZHbNfOinSE8R","name":"Vim & Vigor","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are a virtuoso when it comes to swordplay. It takes little effort for you to size up your opponent, and when the opportunity avails, you make your mark upon their clothing – a characteristic number or letter. This mark is how you and your fabled fencing skills will be known by in history.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you Parry a melee weapon, immediately make an Opportunity Attack against that same opponent. You may only make this attack if you are wielding a melee weapon possessing the Finesse Quality."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Dusk Till Dawn","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are charged with filling your days with funerary needs and your nights warding the graveyard against corpse thieves and tomb robbery. Thus, you have grown accustomed to just a few hours of sleep a night.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Resolve Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, you only need 3 hours of uninterrupted sleep to recover your Peril Condition Track."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ftx0YwrbQVlKFwnp"}
{"_id":"gxo9WggD8JfBmApJ","name":"Fame & Fortune","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Even when the chips are down, a Fop always seems to come out on top. Unlike others, they make their own luck.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When making any Skill Test, you never suffer the ill-effects of Critical Failures, instead treating it as a failed Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"hUWKnLUe7gIcMwHM","name":"Gygaxian Naturalism","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Dungeoneers have spent an inordinate amount of time learning the ins and outs of traps, whether mechanical or human. As a result, they exhibit an uncanny knack for escaping deadly snares and ambushes – invariably by the skin of their teeth.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At any time, you may spend 1 Fortune Point to avoid a trap or other contrivance intended to cause you harm, or cancel the effects of being Surprised following an ambush. Additionally, treat a result of 20% on percentile dice as a Critical Success, no matter whether you would have failed or Critically Failed the Skill Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Psionik Disruption","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Occult Magicians are feared for their ability to rip through fragile minds, and to change the course of the immediate future using mind tricks.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever a Character you can see clearly takes their Turn, you may make a Scrutinize Test as a Reaction for 1 AP. By succeeding a Scrutinize Test, the person you see is Disrupted, and you command them to take any Action In Combat (but it must be a 1 AP action). Should your Disruption cause them to bring harm to their allies, they can attempt a Resolve Test to Resist this effect. Disruption can only affect Humanoids and Mutants (including player Ancestries). You can use this ability outside of combat, but the action you declare cannot exceeds 10 seconds of time to complete it. Finally, the same person cannot be made subject to Disruption more than once in any 24 hour period."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"iJ2hEEh7xhWU8qh2"}
{"name":"Red Baron","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are the ace-of-aces, able to keep even the most ramshackle carriage or airborne dirigible from turning into a heaping, flaming wreck of wood and iron.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may substitute Pilot in place of any Skill required to drive a vehicle, use a boat or ride a creature. Furthermore, whenever your vehicle is Wrecked!, you do not crash. Instead, your vehicle coasts a Distance of 6 yards and stops, collapsing to pieces."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"iJTlqEQ0HoxkdSfA"}
{"_id":"iJVJSFK1xg3OX4jS","name":"Warp Spasm","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"What drives a person to feel more alive at the brink of death? Do they hear the call of ancestors past as the blood flows – or are they simply mad? Are they filled with some primal calling lost to their brethren – or have they simply succumbed to feral urges? Are they driven into a rage fueled by ritual – or are they possessed by a primal god? Do they fight for some greater purpose – or are they simply envoys of chaos? One thing is certain: only the taste of blood will sate their vexation.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you are Seriously or Grievously Wounded, add a 1D6 Fury Die to Damage you inflict with melee weapons."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"iTm6uUJNsqb8jRWx","name":"Shaken Not Stirred","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Play it cool, hold your cards close to your chest and roll the dice only when you are absolutely certain you’ll win. But when all else fails, you always find another in-road for your ambitions.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Charm or Eavesdrop Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"ikyc3m2pWCwOHry3","name":"Coup De Grâce","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"An Executioner deals the death stroke to those that kneel before them.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you inflict Injuries with melee weapons, they are always considered to be Grievous Injuries unless you’re using a weapon possessing the Ineffective, Pummeling or Weak Qualities."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Hex-And-Counter","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"There is a rule for every action on the battlefield, and it took you years to master all those subtle rules, no matter how esoteric.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Warfare Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, whenever the GM intends to spend a Misfortune Point against you, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If the result is face ‘6’, they must use two Misfortune Points instead of one."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"j6Ut710ZibhLgxSc"}
{"_id":"j7HfkI8eErS6F6vo","name":"Road to Enlightenment","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Pilgrim is a spiritual aspirant whose faith secures them a place at the side of those they revere in the afterlife. However, this spirituality can be compromised by the unwanted attentions of Abyssal terrors. Fortunately, their shield of faith safeguards them at opportune times.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you suffer 1 to 3 Corruption, make a (Routine +10%) Resolve Test. If you suffer 4 to 6 Corruption, make a (Standard +/-0%) Resolve Test. If you suffer 7 to 9 Corruption, make a (Challenging -10%) Resolve Test. If successful, you suffer no Corruption."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jQVWa42KhgkTgC4I","name":"Armor of God","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/mailed-fist.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Put on the whole armor of the God-Emperor, that ye may be able to stand against the wiles of chaos.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Armor never prohibits or further penalizes your Difficulty Rating when you cast Magick or Rituals. This also means you can ignore the Heavy Quality for purposes of casting Magick."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jRYQ5el9iMaovvhg","name":"Skin O’ My Teeth","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"In times of desperation, in the most difficult of situations, you’re able to escape... somehow alive. However, the repercussions for the actions you took that got into such a scrap – and out again – will inevitably catch up to you someday.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you use a Fate Point, make a Resolve Test. If successful, you retain the Fate Point."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"jdq348IkHkHnhUGD","name":"Seasons to Pass","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"During certain seasons, your Magick grows immensely in power – particularly when you attempt to draw deeper from the wellspring of Elementalism. You can more accurately guess how the Winds of the Æther will impact your ability to cast, as you withdraw a power untold among other Magickal orders.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you enter this Expert Profession, select two seasons of the campaign world. During the first season, subtract one Chaos Die when you Channel Power. During the other season, subtract two Chaos Dice when you Channel Power."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Covenant Mastery","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Having reached the ultimate stratum of Magickal practice, you have discovered the secrets of your Daemon. Unraveling these devoted mysteries, you call forth unearthly and befouled sorceries at your fingertips, distorting reality around you.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Greater Magick from the Covenant your Expert Profession granted you, provided you possess at least three Skill Ranks in Incantation. In addition, you automatically learn one Greater Magick spell from your Covenant."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"jhVthW86uE6ZWStH"}
{"_id":"jkfLwiYMsXPo8aqs","name":"Blight-born Immunity","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Long has the Plague Doktor wandered among the sick and infirm. Both a life-giver and death-dealer, a Plague Doktor is both an omen of death and a portent to life.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You always succeed in Skill Tests to Treat Disease. In addition, any time you Critically Succeed a Skill Test to withstand Disease, you are forever immune to it in the future."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Cult Indoctrination","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Cult groups often have a dynamic leader whose authority is respected and often unquestioned. Using merely power of their voice, Cult Leaders can erase memories, implant new memories or cajole a frail mind to experience a forgotten event from their past.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You treat the Incantation Skill as a Common Skill for purposes of Hypnosis. By succeeding an Incantation Test, the person you perform Hypnosis on is Brainwashed, and you choose one of three effects to occur:\n you remove a single memory;\n you implant a new memory;\n the person can recall an event that has transpired with perfect clarity.\nShould your Brainwashing impose new beliefs that are dangerous, they can attempt a Resolve Test to Resist this effect. Brainwashing can only affect Humanoids and Mutants (including player Ancestries). Finally, the same person cannot be made subject to Brainwashing more than once a week. Performing Hypnosis can be found in Chapter 4: Liber Alchemiae.\n  "}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"kUntxghWnFOf1NEN"}
{"name":"Bombs Away!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Within your hands, you wield a power that dwarfs all other weaponry on the battlefield. The complex hardware and clever gadgetry of the great war machines are like an extension of your eye as much as your hand, having taken to it like a swordsman does to their blade.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Warfare Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, whenever using Burst, Cone and Explosion Templates with a war machine, you can spend a Fortune Point to not harm your allies after firing the weapon."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"kdZPjbBVvAXX8XqA"}
{"_id":"kiREYvhDSiRwEVkn","name":"Masters of Defense","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether through grueling training regimen or disciplined schooling, you have become a master of military techniques. You expertly avoid blows with ease, eviscerating an opponent’s flurry of blows with steady parries and deft maneuvers.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you are struck by a melee weapon, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If it lands on face ‘6’, you ignore it as you automatically Parry it for 0 AP. Otherwise, you can attempt to Parry as usual. You must be armed with a weapon possessing the Finesse Quality in order to use this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Iron Citadel","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are literally a living bulwark of defense, growing more and more implacable with every strike.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Every time you suffer Damage from a melee weapon, temporarily increase your Damage Threshold by +1 cumulatively, lasting until you are Slain! or combat ends. You must be wearing armor with the Heavy Quality to grant this advantage."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"lW6BbzINlwUhZuCk"}
{"name":"Privy Council","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are likely a member of a private body of advisors who serves a house. You hold an office that requires a deep understanding of politics and bureaucracy, and speak with the authority of your lord or lady.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail an Education or Leadership Test, you can re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ljQzL9lxKPac7MFP"}
{"_id":"ljds02hFT7fkoLFC","name":"Mastermind","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You’re no fool when it comes to interpreting the letter of the law, as you take advantage of the sanctions that support the business and amnesties afforded to ‘lawful’ pursuits. However, when the law falls short, you lean on your lawless roots, resorting to bullying and threats to pave the way to largesse and lucre.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail a Folklore or Intimidate Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"maVaogtd85j7U8QJ","name":"Luck of the Draw","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Gambler feels the ticking of the clock. Being friends with those in the underworld – of many different stripes – does have its benefits. The cards tend to come up aces when needed most.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you use Fortune Points, you do not need to roll percentile dice to make a Skill Test. Instead, you automatically Critically Succeed at the Skill Test you intended to make."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"miXAZIF560buWv05","name":"Infernal Contract","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"While some arcanists may have difficulties beseeching the powers of the Abyss, the Warlock has long-signed away their soul to those creatures. Their master will lend them aid in times of need by sending a servitor demon as an ally.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Anytime you summon Abyssal creatures using a Ritual, you may flip the results to succeed Bargain Test to negotiate for the desired service. In addition, you immediately learn the True Name of one Lesser Demon for purposes of summoning. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Call Demonic Servant."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"mtjpEmF2tCgBVmAd","name":"Sacred Mantra","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Uttering the sacred ‘om’ numinous sound, you can tap into the divine vibrations of the Æthereal Veil. Deep within a spiritual trance, you are able to bend reality to restore vigor and mend your mind, healing both the spirit and the physical body, from within.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may enter a sacred trance for one hour. If you succeed at a Resolve Test at the end of the trance, you expel all Intoxication and Poisons from your system."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Víkingr","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Born on foot or by horse, you quickly leap out of the way from danger... providing you can see the danger coming.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you or your steed are struck by a ranged weapon, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If it lands on face ‘6’, you ignore it as you automatically Dodge it for 0 AP. Otherwise, you can attempt to Dodge as usual. You must be unarmored, or wearing fur or hide to take advantage of this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"mywzJ0orPrKI1z4G"}
{"_id":"npgxNFSipBtTZ78K","name":"Prayers of the Learner","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Veneration of the Learner takes many forms. Some author works of truth; others educate the illiterate. However, Truthsayers take this to an entirely different level – they have learned to sift between truth and lies using divine power.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Learner. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Learner. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Learner until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Learner and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"o51TRjB9qFANUaH6","name":"Warden of the Wild","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/boar.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You much prefer the solitude of nature and creatures of the wilds than the cries and clamor of the big city. As a consequence, you’ve developed an aptitude to not only spot wild animals on the loose, but also to calm angry beasts when they act out of sorts.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you fail an Awareness or Handle Animal Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"oMaZl3vctQB6qWo7","name":"Mastery of the High Arts","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You have successfully unraveled the confusion of the Ætheric Winds, able to ‘separate’ them as you call forth Magick. These strands are then re-woven into perfect, silvery order; their warp and weft woven together to achieve spectacularly perfect feats of Magick.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one Petty, one Lesser and one Greater Magick spell over the course of your Profession. When you succeed at your Incantation Test to cast these spells, treat them as Critical Successes instead."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"oVwiwmBAag8JN5nZ","name":"Arcana of Shadowmancy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The art of deception, concealment and illusion are the backbone of Shadowmancy. As such, you find the darkness and evening fog more comforting than the light and sunny days.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Shadowmancy. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Shadowmancy. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Shadowmancy until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Shadowmancy and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"oyxpGab7dzxD4xzl","name":"\"X\" Marks the Spot","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Grey Guilders oftentimes mark a characteristic ‘X’ upon their religious tokens or clothing, though never where a discerning eye would readily identify it. This ‘X’ is a silent invocation of luck and steadfastness, one that the Nightfather has heard. He marks His blessed followers with an invisible X Himself, as Grey Guilders are unnaturally lucky.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you intend to sacrifice a Fortune Point, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If the result is face ‘6’, you don’t have to use the Fortune Point to gain its benefits."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pKuppJI3koKvWIIb","name":"Turn the Other Cheek","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"So as long as an Adherent makes no attempt to harm another, they are above reproach. But those who walk in blood-stained clothes with a sword at their waist may send the wrong message, allowing others to ignore the Adherent’s pacifist ways.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any creature that is classified as a Humanoid (including player Ancestries) suﬀer a -20 Base Chance to strike you with attacks, until you initiate violence towards them or their allies. In addition, you automatically understand how to use the Ritual of Blessed Sacrament."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pNi0vxs1p3mqaBaq","name":"Master’s Whip","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With every vicious lash of the whip, with every rod unspared and arm broken, the Chattel Slaver continues their disdainful drive to subjugate and oppress.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You ignore the Ineffective and Pummeling Qualities when fighting with Brawling type weapons."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pWvFJ24n3BotVG1V","name":"Magnificent Bastard","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"A Rake lives a riotous life, rubbing elbows with miscreants of all stripe. As the threat of violence rears its ugly head, a vicious punch to the kidney may buy you some time to get away.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one foe in combat. That foe is left Defenseless to all Perilous Stunts you make until they are defeated. You may select another foe afterwards."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"pduaqDaVaDD7OJLV","name":"Prayers of the Crouching One","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The invocations given to the Crouching One are of sanguinity and violence. Priests of their order are able to cause wounds to fester from Ætheric disruption and render death-dealing blows, enhanced by the Crouching One’s power.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Crouching One, as listed under Chapter 10: Grimoire. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Crouching One. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Crouching One until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Crouching One and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"q7YutnSZ5u0MEa82","name":"For a Few Shillings More","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Bounty Hunter is an inscrutable and enigmatic hunter, undeterred by danger. Dogged in their pursuit, they always get their quarry.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"In combat, whenever you make your first Attack Action with a ranged weapon, you never miss. In addition, your intended target cannot Dodge, Parry or Resist the attack. You also add an additional 1D6 Fury Die to the same attack."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"qFSrIA4bn3gwr2Hd","name":"The Final Portent","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The movement of the heavens above reveals secret truths of the world. Interpreting these omens through use of crystal balls, astrology and casting rune stones, you can detect warning signs of endeavors either ill-omened or well-favored by Fortune herself.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one player Character and attempt to foretell their future with an Incantation Test. If successful, when the same ally uses a Fortune Point over the next 24 hours, the Fortune Point is immediately restored to the Fortune Pool. This benefit cannot be given or gained more than once per day."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Blood Oath","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Written in blood, you have sworn an oath against another. Bound by blood, you will ensure that it is carried through to the bitter end.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may voluntarily move three steps down the Damage Condition Track negatively. Unlike Damage done during combat, you do not suffer Injuries from this Damage, but you can enact a Blood Oath against a single foe whose real name you know (or True Name for creatures who are Abyssal or Supernatural). Whenever you use Fury Dice to determine weapon Damage against this foe, they explode on face ‘1’ or ‘6’. You can enact another Blood Oath once the current one is completed by the person being Slain!."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"qjk1QBtsoeUoeFfk"}
{"name":"Weaver of Fate","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Destiny is largely unknown, even to workers of miracles and arcane might. But in the Caravan Mystic, they can sacrifice a sliver of their soul to discover what lies in store for others.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You understand how to use the Ritual of Fortune- telling. Furthermore, you treat the Incantation Skill as a Common Skill for purposes of Fortune-telling. Finally, after successfully using Fortune-telling, the person to whom you told their future gains a Fate Point, which must be used within a month or it is lost. A person can only gain the benefits of the Weaver of Fate Trait once a month."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"r8K7SQ1t03Bmh0Di"}
{"name":"Rawhide!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Don’t try to understand ’em, just rope, throw and brand ’em. Soon we’ll be livin’ high and wide!","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You influence any number of creatures classified as Animals who can see and hear you clearly with Fellowship- based Skill Tests. In addition, whenever you attempt to rustle and coerce Animals and Beasts, you may flip the results to succeed at Handle Animal Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"rD7vBoKQahRBUUx1"}
{"name":"Valorous Aura","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"From how you carry yourself to the impassioned words you speak, your allies are inspired by your very presence.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you succeed at using Inspiring Words, your foes also suffer from Litany of Hatred. In addition, all allies who can clearly see and hear you reference your Percentile-based chances to succeed at Skill Tests to withstand the effects of Stress and Fear."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"rh9stNWO0kmHLRsE"}
{"_id":"sAk8venwJg3ymcXp","name":"Pliers... Scalpel... Bonesaw","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"With an assortment of bizarre and frightening instruments, the Barber Surgeon sees to ‘curing’ the wounded. Where bonesaws fail, the machete can hack through all that sinew and bone to remove a patient’s bothersome, gangrenous limb.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you successfully bind wounds to heal Damage, your patient moves one additional step up the Damage Condition Track positively. In addition, you always succeed at Heal Tests to prepare bandages."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sYoPWq7jkd9BR60K","name":"Maker’s Mark","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Tempered and honed by an experienced hand, the equipment a Guildmaster forges with their hand is strong. Their items withstand the test of time and deterioration, treated almost reliclike in the quality of their craftsmanship.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any time you produce a weapon, armor or shield using your Focus, it gains the Maker’s Mark Quality. This Quality can be found in Chapter 7: Trappings. If the trapping is not one of the aforementioned, it adds +5 Base Chance to Skill use it’s related to (examples include an astrolabe used for Navigation, coach used for Drive, rope used for Athletics, etc.)."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"sedrsLg19nZI966D","name":"White Witchery","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are able to call forth strange, eerie powers from beyond the Æther. Although you do not have a true understanding of where they come from, you pay tribute to older gods nonetheless for such miracles.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select any one Generalist Magick spell (providing that it does not cause harm to another). When you attempt to cast this Magick, you do not need to roll percentile dice to make a Skill Test. Instead, you Critically Succeed at the Incantation Test you intended to make. Furthermore, you may select one additional Generalist Magick spell at both Intermediate and Advanced Tier with the aforementioned limitations."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Purple Hand of Change","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Prince of Change has given you a special, damning gift: the power to understand all Magick in its myriad of forms.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You do not need to spend Reward Points to learn Magick spells. Furthermore, triple your [IB] to determine how many Petty Magick, Lesser Magick and Greater Magick spells you may learn."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"sq9d9AiBbOqIteOj"}
{"_id":"tNJU1L8BPtNFsEYg","name":"The Full Monty","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Prostitutes use suggestive body language, risqué acts and innuendo to convince others to do their bidding.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"All Skill Ranks you acquire in the Charm Skill modify your Base Chance by +20, instead of +10. In addition, when you perform acts of carnal knowledge with another, you both ‘get lucky’, gaining 1 Fortune Point each to personally use. This benefit cannot be given or gained more than once per day."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Trailblazer","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether across rock, snow or ice, you remain undeterred by the rigors of passing over its hardships.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You may flip the results to succeed at Athletics Tests. When you succeed, it is always considered a Critical Success. In addition, when using the Movement subtype of Climb, you do not have to add the additional 1 AP cost."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"tOM71sXImKOMdVNJ"}
{"_id":"tY5k0wVtdikxI788","name":"Mortal Combat","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Pugilists rarely know one end of a sword from the other, but they can rely on their fists and feet to get the job done. Brutal palm strikes, ferocious kicks to the groin and bone-shattering headbutts make up their fighting style.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You ignore the Pummeling and Weak Qualities when fighting with Brawling type of weapons. In addition, you may refer to [BB] or [CB] when inflicting Damage with this type of weapon, whichever is more favorable."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"tccVAuyAYlWDvAgm","name":"Friend of the Wildlands","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Predator or prey; to you, it makes no difference. From the simplest of creatures to the most unfamiliar beasts of a different age, they are all a creation of nature. In that, you have learned to bring them to heel, to speak with them and live among them as their friend.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"For purposes of Skills, Magick and other interactions you have, treat creatures who are classified as Beasts instead as Animals. This means you can tame them, teach them tricks and ensorcell them with Magicks and Skills. Furthermore, when you fail a Handle Animal Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"tjEUVD7yNJjUS31c","name":"Spirit Sight","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You’ve developed an affinity with the Æthereal Veil, as you now exist somewhere between this Magickal membrane and the Material Realm. As such, your sight and Magicks can reach both betwixt the Material Realm and the Veil.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can always affect Æthereal creatures with your Magicks, regardless of whether they are in Æthereal form or not. In addition, you can attempt to visually sense the presence of Æthereal creatures with a successful Awareness Test."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Jailhouse Rock","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Your style of fighting is dirty and chaotic, confounding more traditional martial styles of combat.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you Parry a melee weapon, immediately make an Opportunity Attack against that same opponent. You may only make this attack if you are wielding a melee weapon of the Brawling type."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"trSISNiQvPl5DYT8"}
{"name":"Disciple to Chaos","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You venerate the entire pantheon of the Abyss, undivided in your loyalties. However – of them all – one has taken particular notice of you. Whether this is favorable or not towards your path of Fell Knight is yet untold.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Select one of the following Abyssal Princes: Change, Decay, Pleasure, Violence or the Outsider. You gain an associated Trait from the list below, but must have an infernal holy symbol branded and visible on your body:\n   As an occultist to the Prince of Change, after you successfully use a Litany of Hatred, those same foes reverse their Difficulty Ratings until combat ends (e.g., if they have a Routine +10%, it becomes Challenging -10% instead);\n   As an occultist to the Prince of Decay, your weapons cause Infection whenever you deal Damage. Whenever you Critically Succeed at the Skill Test to strike, your foes also suffer Chaotic Rot;\n   As an occultist to the Prince of Pleasure, foes who are Engaged with you are enraptured by your hypnotic musk and cannot add their Apprentice or Journeyman Skill Ranks to Combat and Willpower-based Skill Tests;\n   As an occultist to the Prince of Violence, when you deal Damage to a foe using a melee weapon with the Punishing or Vicious Quality, they begin to Bleed;\n   As an occultist to the Outsider, when fighting against occultists of the other four Abyssal Princes, you add an additional 1D6 Fury Die to Damage and automatically succeed at Resolve Tests."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"uLcoXnM2IDTuMgUY"}
{"_id":"uOyKz5KqUCa9aMT4","name":"Guerilla Warfare","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Not disciplined enough to withstand a straight engagement, the Militiaman is constantly on the move, using hit-and-run tactics to influence the outcome of any battle. They are able to move across the battlefield without sacrificing their defenses, strengthening themselves against the oncoming onslaught.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You never provoke Opportunity Attacks with Movement Actions or any other action you take. In addition, any Movement Action a foe takes while Engaged with you immediately provokes an Opportunity Attack from you."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Cheshire Grin","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Ministers of Rot always seem to wear a wide grin, even in the hardest of circumstances. It leads to disquieting moments, when others don’t realize that the Minister’s inscrutability may be luring them further into danger.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At your option, you can substitute the Charm Skill in place of Guile. Furthermore, you can substitute Charm in place of any Skill required to Parry melee weapons."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"us7j5xRkODATqF2L"}
{"_id":"vI1kHQWT36rw1ppW","name":"Prayers of the Steward","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Utterances to the Steward are always militaristic in nature. They are ordered, well-structured and highly ritualistic. Breaking any of the sacred rites can cause disruption from the Æthereal, potentially bringing forth chaos due to your fumbling of instruction.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Steward. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Steward. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Steward until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Steward and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"vhTc3N2WZlrkDX3g","name":"Cult of Personality","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Cultist can harness the ever-changing Ætheric Winds as the wellspring of their Magick. They exhibit mastery over the smallest of spells, but ignorance towards others beyond their understanding.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When casting Generalist Magick – at your option – you may automatically succeed at the Incantation Test, but move one step down the Peril Condition Track negatively. You also understand how to use the Ritual of Blessed Sacrament."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"vky9fwIdG3dhtDFe","name":"Pay the Piper","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"When the tax collector makes his demand for recompense, those debts are always paid in full (at the pain of a beating, or worse).","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you fail a Bargain or Intimidate Test, you may re-roll to generate a better result, but must accept the outcome."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"The Bard's Tale","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You inspire great courage and alacrity in arms whenever you belt forth anthems, speak poetry or play ballads upon the battlefield.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When you succeed at using Inspiring Words, allies increase their Damage and Peril Thresholds by +1, and add +3 to their Initiative."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"wWPYnUK0inNJQglb"}
{"_id":"wgWjrxRsoWVTNzJK","name":"Don’t Kill the Messenger","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The timbre in your voice brings a certain comfort during exchanges, turning tense conversations into mutually beneficial ones. Your words are even-handed, appealing to all parties with gravitas and dignity.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When using Fellowship-based Skill Tests, you do not suffer any additional penalties due to differences in Social Class."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"wuTi4MpDqGRZFAqw","name":"Arcana of Astromancy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Those who have mastered the art of Astromancy can sense disturbances within the Æthereal Veil. The disruptions can be understood as omens and portents. Through Astromancy, the Soothsayer can manipulate a person’s destiny, including their own.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Astromancy. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Astromancy. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Astromancy until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Astromancy and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcane types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"wwDCJKxl9MHlXrct","name":"Leaf on the Wind","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/leaf-swirl.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"You are rarely comfortable in one place, possessing a strong sense of wanderlust. You have learned to live off of roots and bark when necessary. The dangers of the wilds persist and just a few minutes of shut-eye here and there are enough to live by.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You are always able to provide enough food and water to live on, never suffering from the effects of Starvation or Sleep Deprivation."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"wxmACrUQuEBl0shd","name":"The Dance of War","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether they use ribbon-trailed spears, graceful long swords or dual scimitars, the War Dervish confounds their enemies with their fast movement and acrobatic pirouettes.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"For every successful strike, Parry or Dodge you make during combat, increase your place on the Initiative Ladder by +1."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"xEahzzuZEme5AEpW","name":"Backbreaking Labor","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Laborer is accustomed to hardship and demanding physical routine. They are the go-to when laborious tasks need to be performed, requiring not only strength, but tenacity and endurance.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You do not suffer the ill-effects of Peril, until you are at “Ignore 3 Skill Ranks” on the Peril Condition Track."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Book of Oaths","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Oathkeepers oftentimes keep a book of ‘grudges’ against others, but sometimes these stories are more inspirational rather than being fueled by hatred of other clans or Ancestries.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can attempt a Skill Test, related to your Focus in the arts, to tell a story to others. If successful, a number of allies equal to your [FB] may either ignore any one Critically Failed Skill Test or treat one Fury Die as a face ‘6’ without spending a Fortune Point within the next 24 hours. If you Critically Succeed, you influence a number of allies equal to three times your [FB] instead. A Character may only gain the benefit of this storytelling once per day, which takes at least an hour of time to perform."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"xnhDMnlkbo9WVLm5"}
{"name":"No Mere NPC","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Although some may mistake you for just another hawker on the docks or greengrocer, you’re anything but. You are a big spender, a wheeler-dealer and know how to distinguish trash from real treasure.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Any object you sell is treated and appraised at its full value. Furthermore, you may flip the results to succeed at Skill Tests to appraise and sell legal goods."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"yLeMXaXgZUCv27dj"}
{"_id":"yic8Yjzf0UqG2ibc","name":"Stand and Deliver!","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Whether robbing from the rich to exact for the poor, or simply robbing for their own gain, Highwaymen always find purchase for their quips where they can be bought or afforded when defending themselves.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"At your option, you may substitute the Charm Skill in place of Intimidate. In addition, you may substitute Charm in place of any Skill required to Parry melee weapons."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zF6rmqhQklHuxkxB","name":"Arcana of Sorcery","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Anointed by the forces of disorder and corruption, Warlocks have the power to inflict suffering upon another with but a word.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Sorcery. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Sorcery. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Sorcery until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Sorcery and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zZ75VdTaW7WPCXFn","name":"Prayers of the Custodian","type":"trait","img":"systems/zweihander/assets/icons/book-storm.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"Terrible dreams haunt the Augur; however, within these dreams comes hidden meaning and secrets. This is the way the Custodian speaks to Her followers, allowing them to prognosticate the future. Through these portents can Her Augurs begin to understand the higher mysteries of the universe and call upon the Custodian’s full body of blessings.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Prayers of the Custodian, as listed in Chapter 10: Grimoire. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Prayers of the Custodian. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Prayers of the Custodian until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Prayers of the Custodian and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Prayer types other than Prayers of the Custodian."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Virtuoso","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"There is a ‘music’ that plays in your head whenever you practice the arts. Matching your brushstrokes, chisel or pen to the rhythm of the music, you create works of art that last not only a lifetime, but will gain acclaim long after you are long gone.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"Whenever you perform or create works of art, roll a 1D6 Chaos Die. If it lands on face ‘6’, you automatically\n  Critically Succeed at the related Skill Test. Otherwise, you can attempt a Skill Test as usual. You must be Unharmed during the creative process to take\n  advantage of this Trait."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"JyjuBRFhP4y9QWxg":3},"flags":{},"_id":"zlUAbwcizKN5S9Ui"}
{"_id":"zuvYCBbVrhn3yhhA","name":"Arcana of Pyromancy","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"From the smallest flicker to the largest of conflagrations, Magick from this particular arcana is incredibly destructive. But you are a master of the flames, commanding massive infernos to spill forth into the Material Realm with but a word.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"You can now attempt to learn Magicks from the Arcana of Pyromancy. In addition, you automatically learn one Petty and one Lesser Magick spell from the Arcana of Pyromancy. You cannot cast Lesser Magick from the Arcana of Pyromancy until you have two Skill Ranks in Incantation. You can continue to learn Generalist Magick. Finally, you may only ever use Arcana of Pyromancy and cannot adopt any other Profession that gives different Arcana types."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"zyLoHaHWQR5G62zR","name":"The Enforcer","type":"trait","img":"/systems/zweihander/assets/icons/vitruvian-man.svg","data":{"flavor":{"description":"The Pledged Guard is duty-bound to protect and to serve their master. Should they be made a target of assassination, an eel pie or even bird droppings, the Pledged Guard will throw themselves into harm’s way to protect their charge.","notes":""},"effect":{"value":"When Engaged with an ally and they fail to Counterspell, Dodge, Parry, Resist or cannot do so, you may immediately spend 0 AP and make a Coordination Test. If successful, they are pushed 1 yard away and suffer no effects. You instead suffer in their stead, but cannot Counterspell, Dodge, Parry or Resist its effects."}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"9cilLhNTlIyJpmtZ":3},"flags":{}}
